FIGURED IT OUT YET.

59
00:06:20,541 --> 00:06:24,458
WELL, WE'RE PERFORMING
ON A VERY SPECIAL STAGE.

60
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:27,125
WE ARE,
IF YOU'LL PARDON THE EXPRESSION,

61
00:06:27,208 --> 00:06:29,708
IN THE THEATER
OF HIS MIND.

62
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:34,625
CONSIDER THESE BOOKS.

63
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:38,250
FOR THEM TO EXIST,
SOCIETY MUST EVOLVE

64
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:40,333
TO AN APPROPRIATELY
ADVANCED STATE.

65
00:06:40,416 --> 00:06:42,791
BUT FOR A SOCIETY
TO EVOLVE,

66
00:06:42,875 --> 00:06:46,500
IT WOULD NEED THE LINGUISTIC
TOOLS THESE BOOKS CONTAIN.

67
00:06:51,625 --> 00:06:54,750
I KNOW-- A BIT OF
A CHICKEN-OR-THE-EGG DILEMMA,

68
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:56,458
ISN'T IT?

69
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:59,333
EACH ONE'S CREATION
REQUIRES THE OTHER,

70
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,000
SO WHICH CAME FIRST?

71
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:03,583
IN THE FACE
OF SUCH A PARADOX,

72
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:06,125
ONE COULD REASONABLY ARGUE
THAT LANGUAGE IS PERHAPS

73
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:08,666
NOT ENTIRELY
A HUMAN INVENTION.

74
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:13,166
IS IT TOO FAR-FETCHED
TO IMAGINE GODLIKE CREATURES

75
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:15,708
BESTOWING MAN
WITH THE GIFT OF LANGUAGE?

76
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:18,708
MMM, IT'S PROBABLY
A BIT FAR-FETCHED.

77
00:07:18,791 --> 00:07:22,916
IT WAS ROUSSEAU WHO FIRST
PUT FORWARD THIS ARGUMENT.

78
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:26,958
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S PROBABLY
ENOUGH PHILOSOPHY FOR NOW.

79
00:07:27,041 --> 00:07:29,041
TIME TO GET BACK
TO THE DISSECTION

80
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:31,375
OF THIS YOUNG MAN'S
PAST AND FUTURE.

81
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:34,375
WHO KNOWS WHAT TREASURES
WILL BE UNEARTHED BY THE--

82
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:37,041
- Male voice:
--FICKLE HANDS OF FATE?

83
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,166
( chuckling )

84
