- ( snaps )
- WHY IS MY NAME ON THE COVER?

85
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,958
WHERE'D YOU GO?

86
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:58,583
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

87
00:08:01,125 --> 00:08:02,708
NO, THEY'RE ALL--

88
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:16,333
I'M DREAMING.

89
00:08:16,416 --> 00:08:20,083
- Male voice: THIS IS NOT
A DREAM, VINCENT LAW.

90
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:23,875
COME, OVER HERE.

91
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:26,625
- WHO'S THERE?!

92
00:08:26,708 --> 00:08:29,125
DOROTHY.

93
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,250
- Male voice:
I AM NOBODY.

94
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,250
EVEN IF I WAS SOMEBODY,

95
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:35,416
I AM BEYOND
YOUR COMPREHENSION.

96
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,916
AND EVEN IF YOU COULD,

97
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,625
YOU WOULD NOT HAVE THE TOOLS
TO EXPRESS THAT KNOWLEDGE.

98
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:44,125
- CHIEF.
- THAT IS THE WAY IT HAS TO BE.

99
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:46,166
YOU ALREADY KNOW THIS.

100
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,458
- ( grunting )

101
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,250
I'M STILL DREAMING.

102
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:57,166
Male voice: THIS IS NOT
A DREAM, VINCENT LAW.

103
00:08:57,250 --> 00:09:00,916
FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF OTHERS
I AM PART OF THE WORLD.

104
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,666
BUT WHEN I OBSERVE THE WORLD
FROM MY PERSPECTIVE,

105
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,541
